==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Literalism
<hw>Lit"er*al*ism</hw> <pr>(l⟦icr⟧t"⟦etil⟧r*⟦ait⟧l*⟦icr⟧z'm)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>That which accords with the letter; a
mode of interpreting literally; adherence to the letter.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Fine Arts)</fld> <def>The tendency or disposition
to represent objects faithfully, without abstraction, conventionalities,
or idealization.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Literalist</ent>⟦br⟧
